Boil a half-full #kettle{}, then pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{}
with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for
~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, then pop it on top of the pan and allow to
steam.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Chicken Thigh{240%grams}(diced), @British Smoked Bacon
Lardons{90%grams} and @Mushrooms{120%grams}(sliced). Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Stir-fry until golden brown all over, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) using a #garlic press{}.

Cut the @Lime{1/2} into wedges.

Once the chicken has browned, add the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet},
@Ginger Puree{15%grams} and garlic to the pan. Cook, stirring frequently, until
fragrant, ~{2%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium, then add the @Mangetout{80%grams}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml},
@Sambal Paste{15%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@Ketjap Manis{25%grams} and @Honey{1%tbsp}. Stir to combine.

> Tip: Add less sambal paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir through the cooked rice and cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice, then remove the pan from the heat. Taste and
season with salt, pepper or more lime juice if needed.

Share the chicken and bacon fried rice between your #bowls{}. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!